Here's a comprehensive .gitignore for a Go project that includes hiding the .github directory:
Copy# IDE configurations
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
*.swo

# Go build and test files
*.exe
*.exe~
*.dll
*.so
*.dylib
*.test
*.out
go.work

# Build output
bin/
dist/
build/

# Go workspace files
go.work
go.work.sum

# Go debugging files
debug/

# Test cache
*.test
*.tmp
testdata/

# Local binary directory
bin/

# Dependency directories
vendor/

# Environment variables
.env
*.env
.env.*

# GitHub Actions directory
.github/

# Go coverage files
coverage.txt
coverage.html
*.cover

# Project-specific binary files
main
myapp
app

# macOS
.DS_Store

# Log files
*.log
logs/

# Air live reload
tmp/